<h3> Note </h3>
<p> By virtue of how nominations work, some winners in pre-Oscars shows do not get nominated for an Oscar (e.g. Ben Affleck for Directing in
 <i>Argo</i>). In such a case, for illustrative purposes, a nominee of both the said pre-Oscar show and the Oscars will be chosen at random. If none are Oscar-nominated,
 a nominee will be chosen at random. Additionally, some awards shows have ties; a winner will be chosen at random. </p>